04) -> z05` has inputs t05 and c04. But c04 is now produced by XOR(x08, y08) instead of OR(a04, b04). So this gate will compute XOR(partial_sum_5, partial_sum_8) instead of XOR(partial_sum_5, carry_4). The circuit is broken.\n\nIn my algorithm:\n- carry = t08 (the output of OR(a04, b04))\n- partialSum = t05 (the output of XOR(x05, y05))\n- Looking for XOR(t05, t08) - this doesn't exist\n- Fallback: findGateWithInput(t05, 'XOR', xorXY) - finds XOR(t05, c04) -> z05\n- The other input is c04, so we swap t08 <-> c04, which is correct!\n\nThe key insight is that we're looking for XOR gates whose input reference includes 'partialSum', and the sum gate XOR(t05, c04) does reference t05 as an input. This finds the right gate regardless of what carry is.\n\nSo my updated code should handle this case correctly. Let me test:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":212,"cache_read_input_tokens":80051,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":212},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ebdcb1a5-364b-42ac-8e44-01432b0cd689","uuid":"1cadd60d-c321-4d98-b445-92405e9aa622"}
